info.readme:
LocalGov StarterKit 5.1.1 ======================== A starter kit for service driven websites. Comes with settings for content, navigation, news, events and contact management. and you can even import existing navigation structures (like the LGNL)
For best results install on a clean install of umbraco 7.3

Template.Design:
@inherits Umbraco.Web.Mvc.UmbracoTemplatePage @using ClientDependency.Core.Mvc @{ Layout = "Master.cshtml"; Html.RequiresCss("//fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Ubuntu:400,500,700|Open+Sans:700,400|Pacifico:400"); Html.RequiresCss("~/css/layout.css"); Html.RequiresCss("~/css/" + Umbraco.Field("sectionStyle", recursive: true)); } @section Metadata { @RenderSection("Metadata", false) }
@Html.Partial("Page/CookieNotice")
@Umbraco.Field("siteName", recursive: true)
    @Html.Partial("Nav/SiteNavigation")
@if (IsSectionDefined("Breadcrumb")) { @RenderSection("Breadcrumb", false) } else {
@Html.Partial("Nav/Breadcrumb")
} @RenderSection("PageHeader", false) @Html.Partial("Components/ServiceAlert")
@RenderBody()
@Html.Partial("Nav/AtoZList")
@RenderSection("Footer", false)
@Html.CachedPartial("Nav/FooterLinks", Model, 600)
The Localgov Starterkit is a Jumoo thingy-me-bob
Localgov Starterkit 5, 2015 » ∞
